Header: raise nav breakpoint from md to lg so hamburger stays visible on phone landscape and small tablets

At the previous md breakpoint (768px) the desktop mega menu kicked in as
soon as a phone was held in landscape (~844px) or on iPad-mini-sized
viewports, which hid the hamburger and left "Book your Roadmap" as the
only visible navigation target on the top right.

Switching the site-header wrapper to lg:flex and MobileNav to lg:hidden
keeps the hamburger through every phone orientation and iPad portrait.
The full horizontal mega menu with both CTAs only shows from 1024px,
where there's actually room for it.
